===============
Oat Cake Recipe
===============
* 200g porridge oats
* 1/2 teaspoon salt
* 1 tablespoon cracked black pepper
* Mixed herbs (optional)
* Chilli flakes (optional)
* Handful seeds (sesame, sunflower, pumpkin etc)
* 50ml extra virgin olive oil
* 4 to 6 tablespoons boiling water

1. Grind 150g of the oats into medium-fine flour 
2. Combine the oat flour with the other dry ingredients in a mixing bowl
3. Make a well and pour in the oil - mix with a spoon or hands until crumbly texture achieved
4. Add the water - form soft dough; sprinkle with oat flakes if necessary or desired
Knead for 30 seconds
Roll to 5mm thick & cut to shape

Bake at 375 F (190 C) for 15 - 20 minutes. 
